currentDoc:
Once upon a time there was an old mother pig who had one hundred little pigs and not enough food to feed them. So when they were old enough, she sent them out into the world to seek their fortunes. You know the story about the first three little pigs. This is a story about the 92nd little pig.

The 92nd little pig built a house out of depleted uranium. And the wolf was like, "dude."

currentSuggestions.original: The wolf thought and thought, what should he do?
currentSuggestions.trimmed: The wolf thought and thought, what should he do?

currentSuggestions.original: So he waited for the pig to come out.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: So he waited for the pig to come out.

currentSuggestions.original: He finally decided to compromise by breaking the pig's legs and letting him bleed out.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: He finally decided to compromise by breaking the pig's legs and letting him bleed out.

currentSuggestions.original: So the wolf must have spent like three days and three nights trying to convince the pig to come out of his house.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: So the wolf must have spent like three days and three nights trying to convince the pig to come out of his house.

currentSuggestions.original: So he decided to not just simply blow the house down but to ruin it in some other way.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: So he decided to not just simply blow the house down but to ruin it in some other way.

ops.insert: The wolf thought and thought, what should he do?

currentSuggestions.original: He carefully placed them so that the house would ignite after enough time and indicated a safe distance.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: He carefully placed them so that the house would ignite after enough time and indicated a safe distance.

currentSuggestions.original: He then lit his end of the house on fire, but it didn't work.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: He then lit his end of the house on fire, but it didn't work.

currentSuggestions.original: He lit them, and then ran back to a safe distance.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: He lit them, and then ran back to a safe distance.

currentSuggestions.original: When everything was in place the wolf struck a match and ran away.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: When everything was in place the wolf struck a match and ran away.

currentSuggestions.original: Then he went to get a match.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Then he went to get a match.

ops.insert: When everything was in place the wolf struck a match and ran away.

currentSuggestions.original: When he tried to jump out the window and ran right into a flaming piece of wood that fell from the fire and hit him in his head
currentSuggestions.trimmed: When he tried to jump out the window and ran right into a flaming piece of wood that fell from the fire and hit him in his head

currentSuggestions.original: But the more he ran around the house trying to beat out the flames, the more fuel he was adding to the fire.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: But the more he ran around the house trying to beat out the flames, the more fuel he was adding to the fire.

currentSuggestions.original: The wolf was like, "he's coming out."
currentSuggestions.trimmed: The wolf was like, "he's coming out."

currentSuggestions.original: But there was no way to put them all out, and the fire burned up the sides of the house.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: But there was no way to put them all out, and the fire burned up the sides of the house.
